iven by heavy, accelerated investments in launch site infrastructure and R&D for the next-generation **Starship** launch vehicle program.\n*   **Connectivity Segment (Scaling & Efficiency):** Connectivity is the company\'s cash cow, generating $7.16 billion in Segment Adjusted EBITDA in 2025. Its capex intensity dropped from 46.0% in 2024 to 36.7% in 2025, demonstrating strong operating leverage. Capex here is driven by steady "higher satellite and ground equipment costs" to grow the Starlink network and support increasing enterprise adoption. \n*   **Consolidated Cash Flow Impact:** Because total consolidated capex ($20.7B) exceeded total consolidated revenue ($18.6B) in FY2025, the company relied heavily on financing activities (generating $26.3B in net cash from financing) to fund its aggressive multi-planetary and AI infrastructure build-out.',
